---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import RelatedPages from '../../components/RelatedPages.astro';
import EditorialAside from '../../components/patterns/EditorialAside.astro';
import serviceMurals from '../../assets/images/service-murals.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why We Start with Discovery, Not Design | Untitled Mixed Media"
  description="Why we start with discovery, not design. Our philosophy on public art, hand-painted signs, and working with intention. Untitled Mixed Media, Richmond, VA."
  breadcrumbItems={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'About', url: '/about' },
    { name: 'Philosophy' },
  ]}
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="pb-0">

    <!-- ─── I · HERO ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="pt-36 lg:pt-44 pb-20 lg:pb-28 px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <Breadcrumb items={[
          { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
          { label: 'About', href: '/about' },
          { label: 'Philosophy' },
        ]} />

        <div class="mt-12 lg:mt-20">
          <h1
            class="font-heading text-titanium-white max-w-5xl"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-5xl); line-height: 0.95; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);"
            data-animate="headline"
          >
            Your space should tell your story. Not someone else&rsquo;s.
          </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-20 lg:mt-32 max-w-3xl space-y-8">
          <p
            class="lede font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
          >
            I believe every mural, sign, and restoration should mean something specific to the person who commissioned it. Not a theme pulled from Pinterest. Not a style borrowed from another city. Something that came from your story, your place, and the people connected to it.
          </p>
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
            data-animate-delay="1"
          >
            A mural shouldn&rsquo;t exist because you have a blank wall. It should exist because there&rsquo;s something about your business, your community, or your history that needs to be visible. When the work arises from that kind of necessity, it carries a weight that decoration never will.
          </p>
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
            data-animate-delay="2"
          >
            That belief shapes every decision I make. It&rsquo;s why I spend time on discovery before I design. It&rsquo;s why I paint by hand instead of printing on vinyl. It&rsquo;s why the finished work feels like it belongs to your building and nobody else&rsquo;s.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- hairline divider -->
    <div class="border-t border-slate-gray" role="presentation"></div>

    <!-- ─── II · WHAT'S WRONG ──────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="bg-midnight-graphite py-24 lg:py-36 px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-x-8 gap-y-12 lg:gap-x-20">
          <!-- Heading anchors the left column -->
          <div class="lg:col-span-5">
            <h2
              class="font-heading text-titanium-white"
              style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
              data-animate="headline"
            >
              What I believe is wrong with most public art and signage.
            </h2>
          </div>

          <!-- Body in right column -->
          <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-8">
            <EditorialAside
              image="/images/content-design/trolley-vintage.jpg"
              alt="A generic streetscape with unremarkable signage"
              position="right"
            />
            <p
              class="font-body text-soft-gray"
              style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
              data-animate="fade"
            >
              Your building shouldn&rsquo;t look like every other building on the block. Your sign shouldn&rsquo;t be the same vinyl sticker your competitor ordered from the same catalog. Your mural shouldn&rsquo;t be a template that could exist in any city in America.
            </p>
            <p
              class="font-body text-soft-gray"
              style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
              data-animate="fade"
              data-animate-delay="1"
            >
              But that&rsquo;s what most of the industry produces. Generic murals designed to photograph well for a week and get forgotten by the end of the month. Vinyl signs cranked out by shops that treat your brand like an order number. Work that adds visual noise to the street instead of meaning. None of it arises from the specific life of the person who paid for it. It&rsquo;s ready-made, applied from the outside, and it shows.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Emphasized closing statement — centered below the split -->
        <div class="mt-16 lg:mt-24 pt-10 lg:pt-14 border-t border-slate-gray max-w-3xl" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="2">
          <p
            class="font-heading italic text-titanium-white"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-2xl); line-height: 1.24; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
          >
            I think public spaces ought to reflect the people behind them. A business owner who poured five years into building something real deserves a sign that carries the same weight. A community with a century of history on its block deserves a mural built from that history, not painted over it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── III · THE ZAG ────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="py-24 lg:py-36 px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">

        <h2
          class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-12 lg:mb-16"
          style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
          data-animate="headline"
        >
          What I do differently and what I refuse to do.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
          >
            I start with questions, not sketches. Before I design anything, I sit down with you and look for what&rsquo;s underneath the surface of your idea. Not just what the project should look like, but what it should mean. I&rsquo;m looking for the thing that makes your project necessary: the moment, the story, the identity that deserves to be visible.
          </p>
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
            data-animate-delay="1"
          >
            I look at every project from three angles: is it creative enough to surprise people, functional enough to work in the real world, and expressive enough to say something authentic about who you are.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The "I refuse" editorial statement -->
        <div class="mt-20 lg:mt-28 relative py-8 lg:py-12" data-animate="fade">
          <span aria-hidden="true" class="block h-px bg-titanium-white w-20 mb-10 lg:mb-14"></span>
          <p
            class="font-heading italic text-titanium-white"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl); line-height: 1.12; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
          >
            I refuse to paint someone else&rsquo;s idea on your wall. I refuse to print your logo on vinyl and call it a sign. I refuse to skip the thinking and jump straight to production. Those shortcuts produce work that could belong to anyone. I&rsquo;m interested in work that could only belong to you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Closing paragraph -->
        <div class="mt-12 lg:mt-16">
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
          >
            What I sacrifice in speed, I gain in depth. I hold to the difficult parts of this process, the deep listening, the slow refinement, because that&rsquo;s where the truth of the project lives. Quality requires patience, and I&rsquo;d rather take the time to get it right than rush to get it done.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Full-bleed image break ──────────────────────── -->
    <figure class="aspect-[21/9] lg:aspect-[21/8] overflow-hidden border-t border-b border-slate-gray" data-animate="reveal">
      <Image
        src={serviceMurals}
        alt="Hand-painted mural in context with its surrounding neighborhood"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
    </figure>

    <!-- ─── IV · WHO YOU BECOME ────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="py-24 lg:py-36 px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">

        <h2
          class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-12 lg:mb-16"
          style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-3xl); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
          data-animate="headline"
        >
          This is what clients tell me after the work is finished.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
          >
            They walk past their building and feel pride instead of indifference. They watch strangers photograph their mural without being asked. They hear customers say, &ldquo;I had to see what this place was about.&rdquo; They stop explaining what their business does because the sign already said it.
          </p>
          <p
            class="font-body text-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-lg); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);"
            data-animate="fade"
            data-animate-delay="1"
          >
            The gap between who they are and how their space looked before is gone. The inside and the outside finally match. The environment becomes whole. Not decorated, not improved. Complete, in a way it wasn&rsquo;t before.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Closing statement -->
        <div class="mt-16 lg:mt-24 pt-10 lg:pt-14 border-t border-slate-gray" data-animate="fade">
          <p
            class="font-heading italic text-titanium-white"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-2xl); line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
          >
            That transformation is what I&rsquo;m building toward on every project. Not just a beautiful wall. A space that finally expresses who you are, built from the truth of your own story.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Editorial text-link CTA -->
        <div class="mt-16 lg:mt-20">
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="cta-link group inline-flex items-baseline gap-4 lg:gap-6 font-heading text-titanium-white pb-3 border-b border-titanium-white hover:border-soft-gray"
            style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-xl); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);"
            data-animate="fade"
          >
            <span>Schedule Your Free Discovery Session</span>
            <span aria-hidden="true" class="cta-arrow inline-block">&rarr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedPages heading="Related" pages={[
      { title: 'Our Process', href: '/about/process' },
      { title: 'About', href: '/about' },
      { title: 'Murals', href: '/murals' },
    ]} />

    <CTABlock />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Drop-cap lede: editorial opening mark */
  .lede::first-letter {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 3.4em;
    line-height: 0.84;
    float: left;
    padding: 0.08em 0.14em 0 0;
    color: var(--color-titanium-white);
  }

  /* CTA arrow glide */
  .cta-link .cta-arrow {
    transition: transform 360ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  }
  .cta-link:hover .cta-arrow,
  .cta-link:focus-visible .cta-arrow {
    transform: translateX(0.5rem);
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .cta-link .cta-arrow {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
